{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn99061530/00332892605/1958022101/1025.xml":{"full_text":"FRIDAY, FEBRUARY 21. 1958\nCLASSIFIED\n.ADVERTISING.\nADVERTISING IN THESE COLUMNS COSTS THREE CENTS PER\nWORD, FIRST INSERTION; ALL INSERTIONS AFTER FIRST, TWO\nCENTS PER WORD. MINIMUM CHARGE IS 50 CENTS. IF YOU\nWANT TO BUY, RENT, SELL, SWAP. GET A JOB. HIRE HELP,\nFIND SOMETHING LOST, THE CLASSIFIEDS OFFER AN EFFEC\nTIVE AND ECONOMICAL MEDIUM.\nHOME IMPROVEMENTS\u2014Roof\ning, siding, garages built, rooms\nadded, baths installed complete,\nbrick and cement work, painting\n\u2022r anything .else you want to im\nprove your home. Pay nothing\ndown, 36 months to pay. See\nCharles Haskett or phone 5704\nElizabeth City. T-8-9-tfc\nOFFICE SUPPLIES. Loose leaf\nledgers, ledger sheets, columnar\nsheets, columnar pads; 200-page\nand 300-page single entry ledgers;\nday books, counter books, type\nwriter ribbon, typewriter erasers,\ntypewriter cleaner, and many oth\ner -items needed for daily use in\nyow office. TIMES PRINTING\nCO., Manteo, N. C. Phone 44.\nVisit ANDERSON\u2019S SUPER\nMARKET-BEACH STORE at\ntwo mile post. Vacation headquar\nters. Open year \u2019round. Write\nBILL ANDERSON\u2019S RENTAL\nAGENCY, KITTY HAWK, reser\nvations, oceanfront housekeeping\ncottages. T-4-8-tfc\nTHE OLD SEA CAPTAIN AND\nDRUMMER Book sl, postpaid.\nGet this racy book of dialogue\nfrom Cape Hatteras and the N. C.\nCoastiand. Send it to your friends,\n6 copies $5 postpaid. Times Print\ning Co., Inc., Manteo, N. C.\nARTIFICIAL BREEDING of your\ncows to purebred, proven stocks\nis both profitable and economical.\nThis service available to family\ncow owners, beef producers, dairy\nherds. All dairy and beef breeds\navailable. Call H. E. Clayton, Bel\nhaven WH 3-3206. P-10-4-tfc\nINDEPENDENT insurance agen\ncies can and will \u201cserve you\nfirst.\" Contact us for yours now.\nHugh Fortescue, Washington.\nTPH-8-29-tfc\nLEDGERS, Office books, loose\nsheets; typewriter erasers, rib\nbons, cleaner, Times Office, Man\nteo.\nFOR AUTO LIABILITY and fire\ninsurance on Hatteras Island,\nSee Ivey Batten, Hatteras.\nT-l-11-tfc\nRUBBER STAMPS made to order.\nStamp pads, daters, inks, etc.\nTimes Printing Co., Inc., Manteo,\nN. C.\nFOR SALE. 8 room, 2 story house,\nMill Landing, Wanchese. Electri\ncity; fine position for sportsmen.\nMrs. Eleazor Tillett, Wanchese, N.\nC. T-l-31-4tc\nFOR SALE: 2 Wisconsin air cooled\nengines. 7.2 and 8.2 H.P. Both\nengines have recently been, put in\nperfect condition. 8.2 HP almost\nnew. Prices $75.00 and $85.00.\nALEX\u2019S REPAIR SHOP, Wan\nchese, N. C. Phone 248-J2.\nT-l-31-tfc\nAZALEAS, camellias, sasanquas\nand many varieties of Chinese\nand Japanese hollies. We have a\ngood selection of -lants at prices\nyou will gladly pay. \u201cWe grow the\nplants we sell.\u201d Nance Nursery, 4\nmiles west\u2018of Washington on Pac\ntolus highway H-2-14-4tc\nSALESMAN WANTED. FOR A\nGOOD PRESENT INCOME, per\nmanent work and secure future\nget into business for yourself.\nGood Rawleigh business available\nin Hyde and Tyrrell Counties.\nWrite Rawleigh\u2019s Dept. NCB-480-\n585, Richmond, Va. H-2-6-4tp\nSAVE YOUR FLOORS and nice\ntile; use plastic and rubber cups\nunder your desk and furniture legs.\nAll sizes in stock. Times Printing\nCo M Manteo, N. C.\nLET US SERVE YOUR FARM\nCREDIT NEEDS. Production\nloans, one year, for general pur\nposes. Loans three to five years\nfor building and repairs, ditching,\npurchase of machinery, livestock\nand land. Washington Production\nCredit Association, Register of\nDeeds Office in Swan Quarter Fri\ndays.* Loans insured at reasonable\ncost. H-2-6-Btc\nARTISTS SUPPLIES. Speed ball\nsets, India ink, black drawing\nink, silver ink, white ink, drawing\npaper. TIMES PRINTING CO.\u2019,\nInc.. Manteo. tc\nADMINISTRATRIX' NOTICE\nHaving qualified as administra\ntrix of the estate of Annie C.\nBenson, deceased, late of Hyde\nCounty, North Carolina, this is to,\nnotify all persons having claims I\nagainst the estate of said deceased.\nto exhibit them to the undersigned\nat her home, Swan Quarter, North\nCarolina, on or before the 30 day\nof January, 1959, or this notice\nwill be pleaded in bar of their re\ncovery. All persons indebted to\nsaid estate will please make im\nmediate payment.\nThis the 10 day of January,\n1958.\nJANIE C. SWINDELL\nAdministratrix of\nAnnie C Benson, Deceased\nH-l-184te\nCO2 fire extinguishers, S2O each\nor two for $35. USCG approved.\nG. G. Bonner, General Supply Co.,\nManteo. Tel. 4-W. T-11-8-tfc\nCAMELLIAS, azaleas, hollies, va\nriety of evergreen plants 1.00\nup; Pyracantha (red berried) 1.50;\nnice flowering trees and shrubs;\nJuniper, Cypress, Arborvitae; Let\nus help you to make your home\nmore beautiful. Roanoke Island\nGardens, Manteo, N. C. Comer-\nMother Vineyard Rd. T-l-24-tfc\nFor your insurance needs see\nW. R. PEARCE, Manteo, N. C.\nAll kinds of insurance\nMAN OR WOMAN\u2014Established\nWatkins Route Available in Bel\nhaven. No experience necessary in\nthis area. Write P. O. Box 5071,\nDepartment S-3, Richmond, Va.\nP-2-6-4tp\nFOR RENT: In home, three room\napartment with private bath.\nAnnie J. Rue, Fairfield, N. C.\nH-2-6-3tp\nTRADE OLD TYPEWRITERS on\nbetter ones at the Times Print\ning Co., Manteo, N. C.\nCOLD, CHAPPED, rough hands\nand skin need soothing, protec\ntive SWISS OINTMENT for cold\nweather treatment. SI.OO at\nO\u2019Neal\u2019s Drag Store. P-2-20-ltc\nOIL BURNER, with blower, tank\nand carburetor for $35. Good\nvalue. Times office; Manteo, -N. C.\nWORK WANTED: Experienced\napartment house manager, motel\nand restaurant manager, desires\nposition in Manteo, or Dare Beach\narea. Write Samuel Dick, Kitty\nHawk, N. C. T-2-21-ltp\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned, having quali\nfied as Administrator with the\nwill annexed of the estate of Julian\nB. Toler, Deceased, late of Dare\nCounty. North Carolina, this is to\nnotify all persons having claims\nagainst said estate to present\nthem to the undersigned in Kitty\nHawk. North Carolina, on or be\nfore the 3rd. day of January, 1959,\nor this notice will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All persons\nindebted to said estate will please\nmake immediate payment to the\nundersigned.\nThis the 30th day of December,\n1957.\nPENNEL A. TILLETT,\nAdministrator,\nWith Will Annexed,\nKitty Hawk. N. C.\nT-l-8-6tc\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nIN THE SUPERIOR COURT\nFAIRHAVEN CORPORATION\nVS.\nJAMES W. SCARBOROUGH, ET\nAL\nTO FREDERICK W. LEWIS,\nGENE F. LEWIS. D. E. MEEK\nINS, ALICE MEEKINS, OTIS\nMEEKINS AND DAISY MEEK\nINS:\nTake notice that a pleading seek\ning relief against you has been\nfiled and the nature of the relief\nbeing sought is that Fairhaven\nCorporation has made application\nto have title to its land, described\nin the petition filed in this pro\nceeding, registered pursuant to the\nprovisions of Chapter 43 of the\nGeneral Statutes of North Caro\nlina, and you are made a party\nbecause you own adjoining land.\nYou are required to make defense\nto such pleading not later than\nthe 3rd day of April, 1958. and\nupon your failure to do so the\nparty seeking service against you\nwill apply to the Court for the\nrelief sought.\nThis 30th day of January, 1958.\n(s) C. S. MEEKINS\nClerk Superior Court\nT-2-7-4tc\nVALUABLE PROPERTY\nOFFERED FOR SALE\nIN MANTEO VICINITY\nThese pieces of proper\nty in Manteo, or nearby,\nmay now be bought at\ngood prices.\nOne corner lot on main\nhighway near school.\n1 6-room house with\nbath, large lot on First\nAvenue in Manteo.\n2 lots, total size 120 x\n120 feet near Manteo\ntown limits in Raleigh\nAvenue, Roanoke Park.\n5 lots near Manteo\nwater plant in colored\nsection. One on comer,\nand near main highway.\nAddress:\nD. V. MEEKINS\nPhone 244 or 44\nManteo, N. C.\n\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nIN THE SUPERIOR COURT\nFAIRHAVEN CORPORATION\nVS.\nFREDERICK W. LEWIS, GENE\nF. LEWIS, LUCY MILLER, DAL\nLAS B. MILLER,, LUTHER\nHOOPER,.. DORA. HOOPER,\nKATHLEEN MEEKINS, CHAUN\nCEY MEEKINS, EUNICE GRAY,\nJAMES W. SCARBOROUGH,\nCALVIN W. MEEKINS, DORCAS\nF. MEEKINS, CARL VENTERS,\nMARGARET B. VENTERS, N. E.\nPRICE SALOMA M. PRICE,\nMOODY MEEKINS, MISSOURIA\nMEEKINS, D. E. MEEKINS,\nALICE MEEKINS, OTIS MEEK\nINS, DAISY MEEKINS,, JAMES\nI. GRAY, LONIE I. GRAY, AR\nNOLD G. TOLSON r INEZ TOL\nSON, AMASA QUIDLEY, BETH\nAN V QUIDLEY, W. M. MEEK\nINS, EMELYS NEEKINS, L. S.\nMILLERS, RHETA MILLER AND\nSTATE HIGHWAY COMMISSION\nTO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN:\nThe parties above named, and all\nother persons interested, will take\nnotice that on the 30th day of\nJanuary, 1958. the above named\npetitioner filed a petition in the\noffice of the Clerk of the Superior\nCourt of Dare County to have the\ntitle to certain lands therein de\nscribed registered and confirmed\npursuant to Chapter 43 of the Gen\neral Statutes of North Carolina,\nand that summons has been issued,\nreturnable at the office of the\nClerk of the Superior Court of\nDare County on the 3rd day of\nApril. 1958. Said land is situated\nin Dare County, North Carolina,\nand more particularly described as\nfollows:\nFIRST TRACT: Beginning at a\nconcrete monument and iron pipe\nin the westerly margin of the right\nof way of the beach highway, and\nw-hich said monument and pipe\nstand due west from the north\nwesterly comer of Tract No. 8 as\nthe same is shown on the property\nmap of Scarborough and McMul\nlan. said map being attached to a\ndeed recorded in Book 45, page\n129. Dare County Registry; run\ning thence with the westerly mar\ngin of the right of way of the\nBeach Highway South 19 degrees\n30 minutes West 2173 feet to an\niron pipe: running thence east,\ncrossing the Beach Highway, 105.3\nto a concrete monument in the\neasterly margin of the right of\nway of the Beach Highway; con\ntinuing thence East 672 feet to a\npoint which is evidenced by an iron\npipe located 5 feet therefrom, on a\ncourse of east, and which said iron\npipe stands in the Park Service\nboundary line; running thence par\nallel to the Park Service boundary\nline South 19 degrees 29 minutes\nWest 209.5 feet to a point which\nis evidenced by an iron pipe stand\ning 5 feet therefrom, on a course\nof East; running thence West 673\nfeet to an iron pipe in the easterly\nmargin of the right of way of the\nBeach Highway; running thence\nwith the easterly margin of the\nright of way of the Beach High\nway South 19 degrees 30 minutes\nWest 281.4 feet to a concrete mon\nument; running thence East 674\nfeet to a point which is evidenced\nby an iron pipe standing 5 feet\ntherefrom, on a course of East, and\nwhich said iron pipe stands in the\nPark Service boundary line; run\nning thence parallel to the Park\nService boundary line South 19 de\ngrees 29 minutes West 906.5 feet\nto a point which is evidenced by\nan iron pipe standing 5 feet, on a\ncourse of East, therefrom; running\nthence West 676 feet to an iron\npipe in the easterly margin of the\nright of way of the Beach High\nway; running thence West, cross\ning the Beach Highway, 105.3 feet\nto an iron pipe in the westerly\nmargin of the right of way of the\nBeach Highway; running thence\nwith the westerly margin of the\nright of way of the Beach High\nway South 19 degrees 30 minutes\nWest 115.3 feet to an iron pipe;\nrunning thence West 796.5 feet to\na concrete monument on the top\nof the dike; running thence with\nthe top of the dike North 14 de\ngrees East 104 feet to an iron\npipe: running thence East 614.8\nfeet to an iron pipe; running\nthence North 19 degrees 30 min\nutes East 906.5 feet to an iron\n'nipe: running thence West 663.3\nfeet to the center line of the dike\nditch, said point being evidenced\nby an iron pipe located 20 feet on\na course of East therefrom; run\nning thence with the dike ditch\nnorthwardly to the northeasterly\nshore of Mill Creek; running thence\nnorthwestwardly with the shore of\nMill Creek to Pamlico Sound; run\nning thence with Pamlico Sound\ngenerally northwardly and east\nwardly to an iron pipe which bears\nWest from the point of beginning;\nrunning thence East 1334.5 feet to\nthe point of beginning. Said tract\nof land is shown on a man of a\nsurvey by W. B. Duke, which map\nis hereto attached.\nThere is excepted from the tract\nof land above described the 100\nfoot wide right of way of the\nBeach Highway.\nSECOND TRACT: Beginning at\na concrete monument situated \u2018on\nthe East margin or right of way\nof the Village Road in and near\nthe Village of Avon, said mnou\nment and beginning point being in\nand marking the Northwest corner\nof the N. E. Price lands, formerly\nknown us the Damon Gray Proper\nty, and said beginning point being\nalso 308.4 feet North 9 degrees\nEast along the West margin or\nright of way of said Village Road\nfrom the middle of the asphalt\nroad leading from Avon to the\nBeach Highway, known as the\nHatteras Island Highway; running\nthence from the beginning point\nalong the Price North line South\n87 degrees East along a line of old\nstakes and posts 632 feet to an\niron pipe and old post in the\nGeorge Meekins Estate Tract West\nline; thence along the George\nMeekins Estate Tract West line\nand along the West side of a dike\nNorth 12 degrees East 418 feet to\nap iron pipe; thence North 87 de\ngrees West 411 feet to an iron\npipe; thence South 9 degrees Wert\n118 feet along a line of old stakes\nTHE COASTLAND TIMES, MANTEO, N. C.\nto an iron pipe; thence North 83\ndegrees West along a line of old\nstakes or posts 254 feet to an iron\npipe in the East margin or right\nof way of said road; thence along\ntfie East margin or right of way of\nthe aforesaid Village Road and\nalong a line of old stakes or posts\nSouth 9 degrees West 310 feet to\nthe point of beginning. Said tract\nis shown upon a map attached\nhereto prepared by David Cox, Jr.,\nSurveyor.\nTHIRD TRACT: Beginning at\nan iron pipe in the westerly margin\nof the right of way of the Beach\nHighway and which said iron pipe\nbears West from an iron pipe in\nthe Easterly margin of the right\nof way of the Beach Highway, the\nlast said iron pipe being located\n1536.5 feet on a course of South\n11. degrees 30 minutes West from\nthe intersection of the easterly\nmargin of the right of way of the\nBeach Highway with the eastward\nprojection of the center line of the\nroad leading from the Beach High\nway into the Village of Avon; run\nning thence from said beginning\npoint so located. West 683 feet to\nan iron pipe on top of the dike;\nrunning thence with the top of the\ndike South 12 degrees 40 minutes\nWest 76.3 feet to an iron pipe;\ncontinuing thence with the top of\nthe dike South 47 degrees 30 min\nutes West 164.8 feet to an iron\npipe; running thence East 787.8\nfeet to an iron pipe in the wester\nly margin of the right of way of\nthe Beach Highway; running\nthence with the westerly margin of\nthe right of way of the Beach\nHighway North 11 degrees 30 min\nutes East 187 feet to the point of\nbeginning. Said tract of land is\nshown upon a map hereto attached\nprepared by W. B. Duke, Register\ned Surveyor.\nThe courses set out with respect\nto Tracts 1 and 3 are magnetic\nfor the year 1957, and the courses\nset out with respect to the second\ntract ar= magnetic for the year\n1952.\nThis 30th day of January. 1958.\n(s) C. S. MEEKINS\nClerk Superior Court\nof Dare County\nT-2-7-6tc\nNOTICE OF DISSOLUTION OF\nROANOKE UTILITIES\nCOMPANY, INCORPORATED\nTO ALL TO WHOM THESE\nPRESENTS MAY COME\nGREETINGS\nTAKE NOTICE that pursuant\nto the provisions of Section 55-117\nof the General Statutes of North\nCarolina, duly executed Articles of\nDissolution by the unanimous\nwritten consent of all the share\nholders of ROANOKE UTILITIES\nCOMPANY, INCORPORATED, a\ncorporation of the State of North\nCarolina, whose principal office is\nin the Town of Manteo, Dare\nCounty, North Carolina (W. B.\nFearing, being the agent therein,\nand in charge thereof, upon whom\nprocess may be served) dated Feb\nruary 5, 1958, has been filed in\nthe Office of the Secretary of\nState, of the State of North Caro\nlina, pursuant, and in compliance\nwith Chapter 55 of the General\nStatutes of North Carolina, en\ntitled, \u201cBusiness Corporation Act.\u201d\nAll creditors of the corporation\nare further notified to file with\nthe corporation statements of all\naccounts and liabilities due them\nby it, pursuant to the provisions\nof G. S. 55-119.\nIN TESTIMONY WHEREOF\nthe ROANOKE UTILITIES COM\nPANY. INCORPORATED has\ncaused this notice to be executed\nin its name and behalf by its Presi\ndent, and attested by its Secretary,\nthis the sth day of February 1958.\nROANOKE UTILITIES\nCOMPANY INCORPORATED\nBv W. B. Fearing, President\nATTEST: M. K. Fearing, Jr.\nSecretary\nT-2-7-4tc\nADMINISTRATRIX\u2019S NOTICE\nNorth Carolina\nDare County\nHaving this day duly qualified\nas Administratrix of the -state of\nWillard Burrus, deceased, of Hat\nteras, Dare County, North Caro\nlina. I hereby give notice to all\npersons indebted to his estate to\ncome forward and make immediate\nsettlement; and those holding\nclaims against the said estate will\npresent them for payment within\nTWELVE MONTHS from the date\nof this notice or it will be pleaded\nin bar of their recovery.\nThis 25th day of January, 1958.\nBRITTIE G. BURRUS,\nAdministratrix\nHatteras, N. C.\n-l-31 r 6tc\nHaving this day duly qualified\nas Administratrix of the estate of\nJames Clayton Tillett, deceased, of\nKill Devil Hills, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina. I hereby give no\ntice to all persons indebted to his\nestate to come forward and make\nimmediate settlement; and those\nholding claims against the said\nestate will present them for pay\nment within TWELVE MONTHS\nfrom the date of this notice or it\nwill be pleaded in bar of their\nrecovery.\nThis sth day of December, 1957.\nHENRIETTA TILLETT,\nAdministratrix\nKill Devil Hills, N. C.\n-l-31-6tc\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nHaving this day duly qualified\nas Executrix of the estate of\nCharles O. Sawyer, deceased, of\nKill Devil Hills, N. C., I hereby\ngive notice to all persons indebted\nto his estate to come forward and\nmake immediate settlement; and\nthose holding claims against the\nsaid estate will present them for\npayment within TWELVE\nMONTHS from the date of this\nnotice or it will be pleaded in bar\nof their recovery.\nThis February 7, 1958.\nMRS. MAMIE F. SAWYER,\nExecutrix\nKill Devil Hills, N. C.\nT-2-14-6te\nDOWN\nTO\nEARTH\nBy\nCARLTON i;\nMORRIS\nEditor, The Index\nGatesville, N. C. iMBUW\nSEEMS AS if TV has a strange\nfascination for almost everyone,\nand even though I could never do\nwithout my newspapers, I find\nsome programs interesting. Others\nare pure hogwash, but then it\ntakes all types of people to make\na world and perhaps they are liked\nby some people.\nBUT THE ADVERTISING is\nout of this world. Along with writ\ning, I also am much concerned with\nadvertising, as it sort of keeps a\nlittle bread and an occasional piece\nof meat on my table. Though I have\nlooked until I have had to change\nmy glasses, I fail to make heads or\ntails to some of the drivel that dan\nces before my weary eyes.\nFIRST YOU see a batch of\nfrankfurters with flames burning\nthem to a crisp and a ball of fire\nleaps and cavorts and dives into\nthe franks screaming \u201csi-z-z-ly\njuicy, si-z-z-ly juicy.\u201d I have never\nseen franks cremated like that and\nhave never bought any on the\nstrength of the ad. I always\nthought juice was something you\ndrank.\nTHEN THERE\u2019S the guy with\nhalitosis. He exudes signals that\nwould put sputnik to shame in a\nsecond. Then he apparently swal\nlows a pill and the signals die\naway and he is happy again, and\nagain I never buy the little pills\nfor I just can\u2019t swallow a pill with\nout water.\nBUT THE WORST one yet is the\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned having duly\nqualified as the administrator of\nthe Estate of Melvin R. Stowe, Sr.,\ndeceased, late of the above named\ncounty and state, all persons hav\ning claims of whatsoever nature\nagainst the said Melvin R. Stowe,\nSr., deceased, are hereby notified\nto exhibit the said claim or claims\nto the undersigned on or before the\n14th day of February, 1959, or this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ntheir recovery. All persons indebt\ned to the said Melvin R. Stowe, Sr.,\ndeceased, are hereby requested to\npay the said indebtedness to the\nundersigned immediately.\nThis the 14th day of February,\n1958.\nLEVIN A. STOWE,\nAdministrator\nT-2-14-6tc\nI How fast can you go in a COFFIN?\nHis leisurely 30 m.p.h. jumped to\n45 as he hit the Parkway 50...\n55 \u201cSpeed Limit 55\u201d He\nwasn\u2019t thinking... 60... 65... 70\nAnother car headed suddenly\ninto the highway and then\nhappened! Quick as B\ncame as I\nunexpectedly, the\n40,000 men, women and children jMBBBBHHpT/\nwho died on our roads. And in 3 out\nof 10 of these fatal traffic accidents, ''J\ndrivers were speeding.\nCan anyone say the few minutes\nsaved were worth the terrible cost? s\nSummer traffic multiplies the iff\nmenace of speeding. Next time\nyou\u2019re tempted to step on it, ask\nyourself: \u201cHow fast can you go in v? J,\na coffinV'\nj\u00df'lls*''\u25a0 site\nS S> V l-*W\njfe jJL\nJBI\nHere\u2019s how you can help stop traffic tragedies:\nDrive safely and courteously yourself. Observe speed limits\nand warning signs.\nWhere traffic laws are obeyed, deaths go DOWN!\nInsist on strict enforcement of all traffic laws.\nTraffic regulations work for you, not against you.\nWhere traffic laws are strictly enforced, deaths go DOWN I\nSupport your local Safety Council\nPublished in an effort to save lives by\nThe Coastland Times\nPhone 44\nManteo. N. C.\nIn toopwstion with The Advertising Council The Nstionsl Ssfety CouncJ\na\nT-2-7-4tc\nguy with wheels and hammers in\nhis head. The hammer pounds and\npounds and his face is blotted out\nand the word PAIN appears over\nhis face and he swallows a pill.\nThen he shouts in a voice that\ncould be heard on the highest\nmountains and deepest valleys. \u201cI\nFEEL GREAT.\u201d It always gives\nme a headache to hear him.\nTHE GREAT fight between buf\nferin and aspirin should be labeled\nas the battle of the bellies. First,\nyou see something that we are told\nis a stomach, though it looks for\nall the world like a Rube Goldberg\ninvention. Then down plunges the\ntwo little white dots and one is\nconveniently an A and the other is\na B. In a split second B gets the\njump on A and is going about his\ndevilish work like a scalded cat\nwhile A is loafing along. Night af\nter night the A\u2019s and B\u2019s and be!\nlies are thrust into our living\nrooms, and night after night the\nB\u2019s win the race. One might al\nmost believe the race was fixed.\nTHE CIGARETTE ads show the\nleast imagination of anything I\nhave ever seen thrust upon an un\nsuspecting public. Camel made mil\nlions by having someone say he\nwould walk a mile for a Camel,\nand all the rest of the cigarette\nworid has tried from that day to\nthis to capitalize on repetition.\nOver and over and over they din\nit into your ears. Like a cigarette\nshould, flip top box, 20,000 filter\ntraps. I smoke a pipe. And I also\ntune to another channel when a\ncigarette ad is coming up, though\nI do get caught occasionally when\nthey stop right at a crucial play\nin a football game to have some\nsexy singer pound a piano while\nshe dreamily sounds off about you\nget a lot to like\nI WILL never believe that a\ncomedian can sell men an auto, and\nthe fact that one was carried\naround the world will never influ\nence me either. But when a bony\nfaced individual steps up amidst a\nhushed stillness so quiet you can\nslice it and carefully spaces his\nwords like an old-time preacher at\ncamp meeting and tells me that it\nis June in January, I know I will\nnever buy a car again. He is so\nsad, I know it would just break\nhis bony little heart to part with\none of his buzzard-wing creatures\nand I wouldn\u2019t dare do anything\nto offend him, for I expect him to\nbreak down and weep at the mere\nmention of parting with it, though\nhe says he is going to do me a\nfavor and let me have it for free\nand will even give me SSOO a\nmonth for the rest of my life if\nHl take it off his hands.\nI HAVE purposely refrained\nfrom mentioning soap operas since\nmy better half is an avid fan of\nthis form of misery. I can only\nsay that I personally, would never\nbe able to use human misery to\nsell my product, and so far I have\nnever known Mrs. M. to be influ\nenced enough to buy any of the\nsoap, though she accepts the corn\nin good faith. And I do not feed my\nboys on cereals, for I want them\nto remain good, old American boys.\nI don\u2019t want any tigers in the\nfamily, for I am getting too old\nto lick tony the tiger, and I don\u2019t\nwant them chasing me out of my\nown home.\nRadio Television\nSERVICE\nand\nREPAIR\nAll Makes and Models\nMANTEO\nFurniture Co.\nPhone 51-J\nANNIVERSARY\nGood Reading\nfor the\nWhole Family\n*News \u00abFacts\n\u2022Family Features\nThe Christian Science Monitor\nOne Norway St'., Boston IS, Mass.\nSend your newspaper for the time\nchecked. Enclosed find my check or\nmoney order. 1 year $lB\n6 months $9 3 months $4.50\nName\nAddress\nCity Zone State\nPAGE SEVEN","height":"25672","width":"18356"}}
